# Documentation maintenance

When adding or changing features, update docs in the same PR/commit:

| Change type | Update |
|-------------|--------|
| User-facing (routes, ingest, corpus, UI, env, local run) | [docs/ARCHITECTURE.md](docs/ARCHITECTURE.md), [docs/ROADMAP.md](docs/ROADMAP.md), [docs/LOCAL.md](docs/LOCAL.md) |
| Chat / workflow / intent / agent behavior | Also [docs/AGENT.md](docs/AGENT.md) |
| Env vars or LLM providers | Also [docs/ENV.md](docs/ENV.md) and `.env.example` files |
| Tests or CI | Also [docs/TESTING.md](docs/TESTING.md) |
| Auth / Postgres / deploy (future) | Also [docs/AUTH.md](docs/AUTH.md), [docs/DATABASE.md](docs/DATABASE.md), [docs/SCALE.md](docs/SCALE.md) |

Do not add redundant docs; extend existing files. Index: [docs/README.md](docs/README.md).
